# Plan: Custom Theme System for T3 Code

## Context

The app currently supports only light/dark/system mode via `apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts` — a module-level singleton using `useSyncExternalStore`. The user wants a richer named-theme system ("t3-dark", "t3-light", "t3-midnight") with per-slot color tokens (sidebar, editor, terminal, status bar) defined in the shared package, applied as CSS custom properties, and surfaced via a theme selector with swatches.

Constraints:
- **No new dependencies**, **no build config changes**
- Preserve backward compat: `resolvedTheme: "light" | "dark"` must remain (consumed by `DiffWorkerPoolProvider`)
- Follow existing patterns: Tailwind CSS v4 custom properties, module-level singleton for theme state

---

## Architecture

### Two-layer model
| Layer | What it stores | Where |
|---|---|---|
| `ThemePreference` | `"system" \| ThemeName` | `localStorage` key `t3code:theme` |
| `ThemeName` | `"t3-light" \| "t3-dark" \| "t3-midnight"` | resolved at runtime |

- **"system"** maps to `t3-light` (OS light) or `t3-dark` (OS dark)
- **Named theme** is an absolute choice (no OS mapping)
- **Migration**: old stored values `"light"` → `"t3-light"`, `"dark"` → `"t3-dark"` at read time
- **CSS application**: `applyColorTheme(name)` sets CSS custom properties as inline styles on `document.documentElement` (higher specificity than `:root`) and toggles `.dark` class from `colorScheme` field
- **`ThemeProvider`** is a thin React component placed at app root; it calls `useTheme()` to subscribe the React tree to theme changes from the module-level store

---

## Step-by-Step Implementation

### Step 1 — `packages/shared/src/theme.ts` (NEW FILE)

Define all theme types and built-in theme data. Pure TypeScript, no Effect dependency.

```ts
export type ThemeName = "t3-light" | "t3-dark" | "t3-midnight";
export type ThemePreference = "system" | ThemeName;
export const THEME_NAMES: readonly ThemeName[] = ["t3-light", "t3-dark", "t3-midnight"];

export interface ThemeColors {
  colorScheme: "light" | "dark";   // drives .dark class + <meta color-scheme>
  // Core
  background: string;
  foreground: string;
  card: string;
  cardForeground: string;
  popover: string;
  popoverForeground: string;
  // Brand
  primary: string;
  primaryForeground: string;
  secondary: string;
  secondaryForeground: string;
  muted: string;
  mutedForeground: string;
  accent: string;
  accentForeground: string;
  // Semantic
  destructive: string;
  destructiveForeground: string;
  info: string;
  infoForeground: string;
  success: string;
  successForeground: string;
  warning: string;
  warningForeground: string;
  // Borders
  border: string;
  input: string;
  ring: string;
  // Extended slots (new)
  sidebar: string;
  sidebarForeground: string;
  sidebarBorder: string;
  editor: string;
  editorForeground: string;
  terminal: string;
  terminalForeground: string;
  statusBar: string;
  statusBarForeground: string;
}

export interface ThemeDefinition {
  name: ThemeName;
  label: string;
  description: string;
  colors: ThemeColors;
}

export const BUILT_IN_THEMES: Record<ThemeName, ThemeDefinition> = { ... };
// (see color values in implementation notes below)
```

**t3-light** — matches existing light palette:
- `colorScheme: "light"`, `background: "oklch(1 0 0)"`, `foreground: "oklch(0.374 0.005 285)"`, `primary: "oklch(0.488 0.217 264)"`, sidebar slightly off-white `"oklch(0.975 0.001 285)"`, editor white, terminal dark `"oklch(0.14 0.004 285)"`, statusBar `"oklch(0.955 0.002 285)"`

**t3-dark** — matches existing dark palette:
- `colorScheme: "dark"`, `background: "oklch(0.165 0.004 285)"`, `foreground: "oklch(0.97 0.001 285)"`, `primary: "oklch(0.588 0.217 264)"`, sidebar `"oklch(0.135 0.004 285)"`, editor same as background, terminal `"oklch(0.09 0.003 285)"`, statusBar `"oklch(0.195 0.005 285)"`

**t3-midnight** — new deep blue-tinted dark:
- `colorScheme: "dark"`, `background: "oklch(0.13 0.025 265)"`, `foreground: "oklch(0.92 0.012 265)"`, `primary: "oklch(0.65 0.22 265)"`, sidebar `"oklch(0.105 0.03 265)"`, editor `"oklch(0.14 0.02 265)"`, terminal `"oklch(0.08 0.035 265)"`, statusBar `"oklch(0.175 0.04 265)"`

All colors mapped to the full `ThemeColors` interface with appropriate alpha-adjusted values for `border`, `input`, `muted`, `secondary`, `accent` etc.

---

### Step 2 — `packages/shared/package.json` (MODIFY)

Add a new subpath export alongside the existing ones:

```json
"./theme": {
  "types": "./src/theme.ts",
  "import": "./src/theme.ts"
}
```

---

### Step 3 — `apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts` (REWRITE)

Replace the existing file entirely. Keep the same module-level singleton pattern (`useSyncExternalStore`) but extend the API.

**Key changes:**
- Import `ThemeName`, `ThemePreference`, `BUILT_IN_THEMES`, `THEME_NAMES` from `@t3tools/shared/theme`
- `STORAGE_KEY` stays `"t3code:theme"` — same key, migrated values
- Add `getStoredPreference()` — reads localStorage, migrates old `"light"` → `"t3-light"`, `"dark"` → `"t3-dark"`, falls back to `"system"`
- Add `resolveColorTheme(pref, systemDark)` — returns a `ThemeName`
- Rewrite `applyColorTheme(name: ThemeName)`:
  - Iterates `BUILT_IN_THEMES[name].colors` and calls `document.documentElement.style.setProperty()` for each CSS var (using kebab-case mapping: `background` → `--background`, `sidebarBorder` → `--sidebar-border`, etc.)
  - Toggles `.dark` class based on `colors.colorScheme`
  - Sets `document.documentElement.style.colorScheme`
- Module-level init: `applyColorTheme(resolveColorTheme(getStoredPreference(), getSystemDark()))`
- Updated `ThemeSnapshot` type: `{ preference: ThemePreference; systemDark: boolean }`
- Updated hook return:
  ```ts
  {
    theme: ThemePreference,         // stored preference ("system" | ThemeName)
    setTheme: (next: ThemePreference) => void,
    resolvedTheme: "light" | "dark",   // ← PRESERVED for DiffWorkerPoolProvider compat
    colorTheme: ThemeName,          // resolved named theme
  }
  ```
- `setTheme` writes to localStorage, calls `applyColorTheme`, emits change (same as before, but with new type)
- `suppressTransitions` + `no-transitions` class logic preserved

---

### Step 4 — `apps/web/src/components/ThemeProvider.tsx` (NEW FILE)

```tsx
import { type ReactNode } from "react";
import { useTheme } from "../hooks/useTheme";

/**
 * Anchors the theme store into the React tree so theme-driven
 * re-renders flow top-down from the app root. The theme system
 * works without this wrapper (module-level singleton), but
 * placing it at root ensures consistent render ordering.
 */
export function ThemeProvider({ children }: { children: ReactNode }) {
  useTheme(); // subscribe to module-level store from tree root
  return <>{children}</>;
}
```

---

### Step 5 — `apps/web/src/components/ThemeSelector.tsx` (NEW FILE)

A grid of selectable theme cards, each with a color swatch preview.

```tsx
import { BUILT_IN_THEMES, THEME_NAMES } from "@t3tools/shared/theme";
import { useTheme } from "../hooks/useTheme";

// Options: "system" auto-card + 3 named themes
// Layout: 2-column responsive grid

interface SwatchProps {
  colors: ThemeColors;  // from the theme definition
}
function ThemeSwatch({ colors }: SwatchProps) {
  // 48×34px preview rectangle:
  //   - full background fill
  //   - thin left strip in sidebar color (6px wide)
  //   - thin bottom bar in statusBar color (5px tall)
  //   - small accent dot in primary color (top-right)
  return (
    <div style={{ background: colors.background }} className="relative h-[34px] w-12 overflow-hidden rounded-md border border-black/10">
      <div style={{ background: colors.sidebar }} className="absolute inset-y-0 left-0 w-1.5" />
      <div style={{ background: colors.statusBar }} className="absolute inset-x-0 bottom-0 h-1" />
      <div style={{ background: colors.primary }} className="absolute right-1 top-1 h-2 w-2 rounded-full" />
    </div>
  );
}

export function ThemeSelector() {
  const { theme, setTheme } = useTheme();
  // Renders "System" card + one card per THEME_NAMES entry
  // Each card: <ThemeSwatch> + label + description
  // Active card: border-primary/60 bg-primary/8 (matches existing settings style)
  // Inactive card: border-border bg-background hover:bg-accent
  // "System" card uses t3-light swatch on left, t3-dark swatch on right (split preview)
}
```

---

### Step 6 — `apps/web/src/index.css` (MODIFY)

**a) Add new CSS variable defaults to `:root`** (fallback values if JS hasn't run):
```css
/* Extended theme slots */
--sidebar: var(--card);
--sidebar-foreground: var(--foreground);
--sidebar-border: var(--border);
--editor: var(--background);
--editor-foreground: var(--foreground);
